g2:c.PROCEDURE.g2:a.TEXT: get-pretty-button-attribute-names(Button : class item) = (text) cdg-filter: symbol = the symbol cdg-target-or-sender-filter; cdg-loaded: truth-value = false; begin cdg-loaded = _opcs-check-for-cdg (); if Button is an sc-target-filter then return "Target" else if Button is an sc-sender-filter then return "Sender" else if cdg-loaded and Button is an instance of the class named by (cdg-filter) then return "Target or Sender" else if Button is an sc-class-filter then return "Class" else if Button is an sc-containment-filter then return "Containment" else return "none" end

get-button-group-name(Button : class sc-toggle-button) = (symbol ) cdg-filter: symbol = the symbol cdg-target-or-sender-filter; cdg-loaded: truth-value = false; begin cdg-loaded = _opcs-check-for-cdg (); if Button is an sc-smh-subscriber then return the symbol message-servers else if cdg-loaded and Button is an instance of the class named by (cdg-filter) then return the symbol object-filters { target-or-sender-filters} else if Button is an sc-target-filter then return the symbol object-filters { target-filters } else if Button is an sc-sender-filter then return the symbol object-filters {sender-filters} else if Button is an sc-priority-filter then return the symbol Priority-filters else if Button is an sc-category-filter then return the symbol category-filter else if Button is an sc-class-filter or Button is an sc-containment-filter then return the symbol object-filters else return the symbol other end

c.OPFO-STRIPPABLE-COMMENT.g2:a.TEXT: 10/20/97 DVG Added custom code for renaming a module, the default code (supplied by Cambridge, bug has been enetered) renames the module but screws up the module hierarchy.

10/28/97 DVG In the menu callback procedures _opcsui-import-map-callback and _opcsui-export-map-callback commented out the code for win32, vms, and unix that sets the default-directory of the Settings object. On a win32 platform the value was getting set to "" but when the dialog was displayed the value c:\. was being put in, by specifying c:\ in the Settings object (_opcsui-import-domain-map-dialog-settings and _opcsui-export-domain-map-dialog-settings respectively) the period is not diplayed and importing and exporting from the c:\ drive will work.
10/28/97 DVG Updated _opcsui-view-browser-callback to fix the uil-dialog-title problem on the browser.

07/14/98 WSM Bug fix HQ-2034081. Removed the code that deleted Node after the prompt-for-delete procedure was being called within the procedure _opcsui-delete-instance. There was no need to delete this object. This error also existed in OpEx 2.1 Rev. 0, but was not uncovered until now.

07/14/98 WSM Bug fix HQ-2034081. In relation to this bug in the procedure _opcsrui-tree-view-message-selection I changed the type of Node from g2ui-file-tree-view-object to item-or-value (the type returned by g2ui-file-tree-view-get-node.
